## Folder structure (3-level max)

```
src/
  app/          Routing only — no business logic
  features/     All domain logic (auth, billing, dashboard…)
  components/   Shared UI components only
  lib/          Shared utilities (api-client, formatters)
  config/       Environment variables and constants
```

## Always follow these rules

- TypeScript strict mode. Never use `any`.
- Files: kebab-case. Components: PascalCase. Functions: camelCase.
- File suffix by role: `.service.ts` · `.types.ts` · `.test.ts` · `.schema.ts` · `.hook.ts`
- Max file size: 300 lines. Split files with multiple responsibilities.
- Use `@/` path alias. Never use `../../..` relative imports.
- No barrel files (`index.ts` re-exports). Import directly from source.
- Features do not import from each other. Compose only in `src/app/`.
- Never create `utils.ts`, `helpers.ts`, `misc.ts`.
- Run `pnpm test` after every non-trivial change.
